<subSubSection id="C368652E93548E09F2AAFE11FC94FE0A" pageId="13" pageNumber="497" type="description">
<paragraph id="8BCD36A593548E09F2AAFE11FC94FE0A" blockId="13.[151,1436,387,702]" pageId="13" pageNumber="497">
<materialsCitation id="3B1A3CF893548E09F2AAFE11FC93FE0A" ID-GBIF-Occurrence="3798147336" collectorName="J. Serrano" pageId="13" pageNumber="497" specimenCount="2" typeStatus="lectotype">
The specimen here designated as 
<typeStatus id="54C9880793548E09F02FFE11FDA8FE56" box="[530,633,387,413]" pageId="13" pageNumber="497">lectotype</typeStatus>
is a male bearing labels “ 
<taxonomicName id="4C724D2693548E09F1A0FE16FBCDFE56" authorityName="Dejean" authorityYear="1829" box="[925,1052,388,413]" class="Insecta" family="Carabidae" genus="Stenolophus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="13" pageNumber="497" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="marginatus">
<emphasis id="B906EAB793548E09F1A0FE16FBCDFE56" box="[925,1052,388,413]" italics="true" pageId="13" pageNumber="497">marginatus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
m. in Hispania”, “ 
<typeStatus id="54C9880793548E09F6D0FE11FAB2FE56" box="[1261,1379,387,413]" pageId="13" pageNumber="497">Lectotype</typeStatus>
” and “ 
<taxonomicName id="4C724D2693548E09F299FE35FD9FFE0A" authority="Dejean, 1829" authorityName="Dejean" authorityYear="1829" box="[164,590,423,449]" class="Insecta" family="Carabidae" genus="Stenolophus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="13" pageNumber="497" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="marginatus">
<emphasis id="B906EAB793548E09F299FE35FE62FE0A" box="[164,435,423,449]" italics="true" pageId="13" pageNumber="497">Stenolophus marginatus</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation id="EFE34B5493548E09F384FE35FD9FFE0A" author="Dejean, P. F. M. A." box="[441,590,423,449]" pageId="13" pageNumber="497" refId="ref10732" refString="Dejean, P. F. M. A. (1829) Species general des coleopteres de la collection de M. le Comte Dejean. Tome quatrieme. Mequignon- Marvis, Paris, vii + 520 pp." type="book" year="1829">Dejean, 1829</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
desig. by 
<collectorName id="2687537393548E09F0FCFE3AFCE6FE0A" box="[705,823,423,450]" pageId="13" pageNumber="497">J. Serrano</collectorName>
”
</materialsCitation>
.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="C368652E93548E09F2FAFE59FBEFFD52" pageId="13" pageNumber="497" type="reference_group">
<paragraph id="8BCD36A593548E09F2FAFE59FC23FD9A" blockId="13.[151,1436,387,702]" pageId="13" pageNumber="497">
<taxonomicName id="4C724D2693548E09F2FAFE59FEEDFE2E" authorityName="Motschulsky" authorityYear="1855" box="[199,316,459,485]" class="Insecta" family="Carabidae" genus="Egadroma" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="13" pageNumber="497" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B906EAB793548E09F2FAFE59FEEDFE2E" box="[199,316,459,485]" italics="true" pageId="13" pageNumber="497">Egadroma</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is currently considered as a subgenus of 
<taxonomicName id="4C724D2693548E09F129FE59FC4CFE2E" authorityName="Dejean" authorityYear="1821" box="[788,925,459,485]" class="Insecta" family="Carabidae" genus="Stenolophus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="13" pageNumber="497" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B906EAB793548E09F129FE59FC4CFE2E" box="[788,925,459,485]" italics="true" pageId="13" pageNumber="497">Stenolophus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(( 
<bibRefCitation id="EFE34B5493548E09F18BFE59FB11FE2E" author="Jaeger, B. &amp; Kataev, B. M." box="[950,1216,459,486]" pageId="13" pageNumber="497" pagination="1837" refId="ref10991" refString="Jaeger, B. &amp; Kataev, B. M. (2017) Subtribe Stenolophina Kirby, 1837. In: Lobl, I. &amp; Lobl, D. (Eds.), Catalogue of Palaearctic Coleoptera. Vol. 1. Revised and Updated Edition. Brill, Leiden, pp. 562 - 577." type="book chapter" year="2017">Jaeger &amp; Kataev, 2017</bibRefCitation>
). However, 
<bibRefCitation id="EFE34B5493548E09F775FE59FF33FDC2" author="Jeannel, R." pageId="13" pageNumber="497" pagination="572 - 1173" refId="ref11231" refString="Jeannel, R. (1942) Coleopteres carabiques. Deuxieme partie. Faune de France 40. Librairie de la Faculte des Sciences, Paris, pp. 572 - 1173." type="book chapter" year="1942">Jeannel (1942)</bibRefCitation>
ranked 
<taxonomicName id="4C724D2693548E09F303FE7DFE62FDC2" authorityName="Motschulsky" authorityYear="1855" box="[318,435,495,521]" class="Insecta" family="Carabidae" genus="Egadroma" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="13" pageNumber="497" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B906EAB793548E09F303FE7DFE62FDC2" box="[318,435,495,521]" italics="true" pageId="13" pageNumber="497">Egadroma</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
to the genus status based on the aedeagus poorly sclerotized and the groove on hind tarsomeres. 
<bibRefCitation id="EFE34B5493548E09F33CFD81FE61FDE6" author="Serrano, J." box="[257,432,531,557]" pageId="13" pageNumber="497" pagination="119 - 129" refId="ref12259" refString="Serrano, J. (1981 a) A chromosome study of Spanish Bembidiidae and other Caraboidea (Coleoptera, Adephaga). Genetica, 57, 119 - 129. https: // doi. org / 10.1007 / BF 00131237" type="journal article" year="1981">Serrano (1981a</bibRefCitation>
, b) added to these characters the observations on male achiasmatic meiosis. More taxa of 
<taxonomicName id="4C724D2693548E09F2AAFDA5FEF1FD9A" authorityName="Dejean" authorityYear="1821" box="[151,288,567,593]" class="Insecta" family="Carabidae" genus="Stenolophus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="13" pageNumber="497" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B906EAB793548E09F2AAFDA5FEF1FD9A" box="[151,288,567,593]" italics="true" pageId="13" pageNumber="497">Stenolophus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName id="4C724D2693548E09F36BFDA5FE1AFD9A" authorityName="Motschulsky" authorityYear="1855" box="[342,459,567,593]" class="Insecta" family="Carabidae" genus="Egadroma" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="13" pageNumber="497" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B906EAB793548E09F36BFDA5FE1AFD9A" box="[342,459,567,593]" italics="true" pageId="13" pageNumber="497">Egadroma</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
must be studied to corroborate these differences.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BCD36A593548E09F2FAFDC9FBEFFD52" blockId="13.[151,1436,387,702]" pageId="13" pageNumber="497">
<materialsCitation id="3B1A3CF893548E09F2FAFDC9FBEBFD52" ID-GBIF-Occurrence="3798147333" country="Spain" location="west Palearctic" pageId="13" pageNumber="497" specimenCount="1" typeStatus="lectotype">
The 
<typeStatus id="54C9880793548E09F2C1FDC9FEB2FDBE" box="[252,355,603,629]" pageId="13" pageNumber="497">lectotype</typeStatus>
hereby designated was collected in 
<collectingCountry id="F365763593548E09F13EFDC9FC97FDBE" box="[771,838,603,629]" name="Spain" pageId="13" pageNumber="497">Spain</collectingCountry>
, the first place mentioned by Dejean. The species is easily identified as it is the single representative of the genus in the 
<location id="8EAD607E93548E09F1B0FD12FBEBFD52" LSID="urn:lsid:plazi:treatment:03DB87B393548E09F2AAFEA9FBB1FD76:8EAD607E93548E09F1B0FD12FBEBFD52" box="[909,1082,639,666]" country="Spain" name="west Palearctic" pageId="13" pageNumber="497">west Palearctic</location>
</materialsCitation>
.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="C368652E93548E09F2FAFD36FBB1FD76" box="[199,1120,675,702]" pageId="13" pageNumber="497" type="description">
<paragraph id="8BCD36A593548E09F2FAFD36FBB1FD76" blockId="13.[151,1436,387,702]" box="[199,1120,675,702]" pageId="13" pageNumber="497">
It is recorded from Africa, the Oriental region and 
<collectingCountry id="F365763593548E09F0C0FD31FC91FD76" box="[765,832,675,701]" name="China" pageId="13" pageNumber="497">China</collectingCountry>
(
<bibRefCitation id="EFE34B5493548E09F172FD31FB85FD76" author="Jaeger, B. &amp; Kataev, B. M." box="[847,1108,675,702]" pageId="13" pageNumber="497" pagination="1837" refId="ref10991" refString="Jaeger, B. &amp; Kataev, B. M. (2017) Subtribe Stenolophina Kirby, 1837. In: Lobl, I. &amp; Lobl, D. (Eds.), Catalogue of Palaearctic Coleoptera. Vol. 1. Revised and Updated Edition. Brill, Leiden, pp. 562 - 577." type="book chapter" year="2017">Jaeger &amp; Kataev, 2017</bibRefCitation>
).
</paragraph>
